-- England Reduces Pakistan to 37-6 on Opening Day of Second Cricket Test
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-08-06T12:10:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/england-reduces-pakistan-to-37-6-on-opening-day-of-second-cricket-test.html

          
          
             England reduced Pakistan to 37-6 at
lunch on the opening day of their second cricket Test at
Edgbaston in Birmingham.  
 Stuart Broad is 3-12 for England, while Steve Finn is 2-10
and James Anderson is 1-12. Umar Akmal scored 17 for Pakistan,
which batted after winning the toss.  
 England won the opener of the four-Test series by 354 runs
at Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  
          
          


  


        